sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1163110
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Emiel van der Kouwe
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter from E. coli that controls the YncE gene, involved in iron uptake and iron sensitive.
FUR (Ferric Uptake Regulation) is a transcriptional repressor of genes involved in iron homeostasis. In presence of iron, the FUR protein changes its conformation and dimerizes. This leads to the binding to the DNA on a FUR binding site, thus inhibiting the mRNA transcription.
Why would you use this part?
This promoter allows you to have an iron-sensitive behaviour. In fact, in the presence of iron, the YncE promoter region decreases the expression of the downstream gene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We blindly extracted the 300 bp sequence upstream of the YncE gene in E. coli. It contains a putative FUR binding site and a putative RBS.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K174016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: The Newcastle 2009 iGEM team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part purely holds the binding site for ArsR protein which can be released when bound to different metals. Hence this part can be combined with any promoter to sense metals that can bind to ArsR protein. When added in front of a promoter with another metal sensor's protein's binding site, it can form an AND gate to sensitively detect specific metals.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was developed mainly to use combinatorial approaches for metal sensing.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We digested the promoter responsive to Arsenic(BBa_K174015) with EcoRI and SpeI and digested the GFP plasmid (BBa_I13401) with XbaI and PstI. sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K174017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CadA promoter with CzrA binding site
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: The Newcastle 2009 iGEM team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
In ''B. subtilis'' CadA system works as an efflux system to take the metals out in the cell. It is normally repressed by CzrA repressor protein. When certain metals get inside the cell, they can bind to CzrA and derepress the promoter expressing CadA. Hence metals are taken out by the efflux system.
By taking the promoter of CadA system, we created a generic metal sensor. Hence when it is combined with coding sequences of other genes, it will regulate the expression of these genes upon sensing metals.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was developed mainly to use combinatorial approaches for metal sensing
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It is taken from ''B. subtilis'' ''cadA'' promoter.
